                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.124a/95: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reber</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-17T14:00:00-00:44"
                            >September 17, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. Department’s telegram No. 70, August 21, 4 p.m. Dr. Smith sails tomorrow to
                    visit neighboring countries as instructed. He expects to be absent about 23
                    days.</p>
                <p>The President said to him yesterday that when arrangements providing for a more
                    permanent medical adviser were concluded, he hoped that Dr. Smith would remain
                    for another period.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reber</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
